What is Git?
Git is a version control system.

It helps:
Track changes in code
Go back to old versions
Work safely without losing code
Collaborate with others

Example:
If your project breaks today, Git lets you go back to yesterday’s working code.

What is GitHub?
GitHub is an online platform that stores Git repositories.

Git = tool (installed on your computer)
GitHub = cloud storage + collaboration website

Used for:
Storing projects online
Sharing code
Teamwork
Showing projects to recruiters

Key Git Terms (Very Important)
Term	Meaning
Repository (Repo)	Project folder tracked by Git
Commit	Saved snapshot of changes
Branch	Parallel version of code
Master/Main	Default branch
Clone	Copy repo from GitHub to local system
Push	Upload local code to GitHub
Pull	Download latest code from GitHub
Merge	Combine branches
Staging Area	Area before commit

Git Workflow:
mathematica
Copy code
Working Directory → Staging Area → Repository → GitHub

Commands:
Edit file
git add
git commit
git push

Basic Git Commands:
:- Check Git version

git --version
:- Configure Git (One time)

git config --global user.name "Keshav Kumar"
git config --global user.email "youremail@gmail.com"
:- Initialize Git repo
git init

:- Check file status
git status

:- Add files to staging
git add file.txt
git add .

:- Commit changes
git commit -m "First commit"

GitHub Basics (Step-by-Step)
:- Create GitHub Repository
Go to github.com
Click New Repository
Give name → Create

:- Connect Local Repo to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git

:- Push code to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
Clone, Pull & Push

:- Clone Repo
bash
Copy code
git clone repo-url

:- Pull Latest Changes
bash
Copy code
git pull origin main

:- Push Changes
bash
Copy code
git push origin main
Branching Basics

:- Create new branch
git branch feature1

:- Switch branch
git checkout feature1

:- Merge branch
git checkout main
git merge feature1

Why Git & GitHub Are Important:- 
Required for:
Projects
Internships
Placements
Open-source
Team work
Resume & portfolio

